@(11-20=c40829.A.11) @q[Inana,self]{“I will send a messenger to the shepherd: let him treat me to the best butter and the best milk! I will send a messenger to my farmer: let him treat me to …… and wine! I, the lady, will send a messenger to the fowler, whose bird-nets are spread out: let him treat me to fine birds! I, @wDN{Inana}, will send a messenger to the fisherman too whose nets are set up in the reedbeds: let him treat me to fat carp!”

@(21-32=c40829.A.21) One of her ushers brought the gifts. The fowler brought choice birds, and the fisherman brought fat carp and put them …… my lady. The shepherd carried butter in his hands, @wDN{Dumuzid} carried milk on his shoulders. He carried butter and milk in containers on his shoulders, he carried milk in the churn on his shoulders. …… called out to the house; @wDN{Dumuzid} ……: @q[Dumuzid,Inana]{“Open the house, my lady! Open the house!”
